# Example config/logbook.env - copy to config/logbook.env (LOCAL, gitignored) to
# opt this firstmate home into the logbook attention board (AGENTS.md section 15).
#
# logbook is a local, loopback-only "what needs you" board that firstmate FEEDS:
# it pushes every pending decision / ready action / FYI as an item and reconciles
# the whole board at session start. As of Phase 2 the loop is two-way: the captain
# can answer a card on the board (or still in chat) and firstmate acts on it and
# clears the card, via an inbound poll shim on the existing watcher check rail (see
# LOGBOOK_DRY_RUN below and AGENTS.md section 15). The tool ships for every user but
# is inert until a truthy LOGBOOK_ENABLE turns it on here, so a non-adopter sees
# zero change.
#
# An explicit environment variable always wins over the value set here. Truthy
# means anything other than unset/empty/0/false/no/off.

# Turn logbook on for this home. Absent, empty, or a falsy value keeps it off.
LOGBOOK_ENABLE=1

# The board's base URL. Default: http://127.0.0.1:8137 (loopback only; a trailing
# slash is trimmed). The tool never binds to anything but 127.0.0.1 by design, so
# do not point this at a non-loopback host.
#LOGBOOK_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8137

# Bearer token the client scripts send on every /api/* call, and that firstmate
# passes to the server when it launches it. Set this to a private value so other
# local processes cannot drive your board. If unset, the server generates and
# persists its own token - but then firstmate's pushes cannot authenticate, so set
# it explicitly when you opt in.
#LOGBOOK_TOKEN=change-me-to-a-private-token

# Where the logbook tool is cloned. Default: <this home>/projects/logbook. Point
# this elsewhere if the standalone tool lives outside projects/.
#LOGBOOK_TOOL_DIR=/absolute/path/to/logbook

# Port the server listens on (host is always 127.0.0.1). When unset, it is derived
# from the port in LOGBOOK_URL (falling back to 8137 when the URL carries no
# explicit port), so you normally never need to set this. Set it only to bind a
# port that intentionally differs from the one in LOGBOOK_URL.
#LOGBOOK_PORT=8137

# Preview / dry-run: when truthy, fm-logbook-push/sync/resolve/ack compose their
# JSON body and record it to state/logbook-outbox/<name>.json instead of posting -
# no network and no token needed. Handy for safe end-to-end testing. (The inbound
# fm-logbook-poll needs no dry-run switch: it is read-only against the board.)
#LOGBOOK_DRY_RUN=1
